                                        <div class="elementor-widget-container">
                                            <p>In order to enhance academic and social interaction, Participants are grouped into Study Group (SG). The Study Group meetings provide an opportunity for the participants of each group to exchange ideas on any lecture deliver and to prepare group papers. Should any aspect of a lecture merit policy decisions, the SGs may put a succinct paper providing policy position for the attention of the Government where deemed necessary. Similarly, they may make an appropriate recommendation(s) for research to be conducted on any matter arising from a lecture.</p>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>
                    <section class="elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-294356a elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default" data-id="294356a" data-element_type="section">
